begemotWlan.description: The Begemot MIB for managing IEEE802.11 interfaces.

WlanMgmtReasonCode.name: WlanMgmtReasonCode
WlanMgmtReasonCode.description: Enumeration of reason and codes used in IEEE802.11 management frames to indicate why an action took place.

WlanMgmtMeshReasonCode.name: WlanMgmtMeshReasonCode
WlanMgmtMeshReasonCode.description: Enumeration of reason and codes used in IEEE802.11 mesh routing management frames to indicate why an action took place.

WlanMgmtStatusCode.name: WlanMgmtStatusCode
WlanMgmtStatusCode.description: Enumeration of reason and codes used in IEEE802.11 management frames to indicate what the result of an operation is.

WlanIfaceDot11nPduType.name: WlanIfaceDot11nPduType
WlanIfaceDot11nPduType.description: Enumeration of values for PDU transmit/receive enabled.

WlanPeerCapabilityFlags.name: WlanPeerCapabilityFlags
WlanPeerCapabilityFlags.description: A list of capability bits that may be advertised by a peer.

WlanIfPhyMode.name: WlanIfPhyMode
WlanIfPhyMode.description: A list of wireless PHY operating modes.

wlanInterfaceTable.name: wlanInterfaceTable
wlanInterfaceTable.description: A table that contains the list of cloned wireless interfaces created on the system.

wlanInterfaceEntry.name: wlanInterfaceEntry
wlanInterfaceEntry.description: Information for a cloned wireless interface.

wlanIfaceIndex.name: wlanIfaceIndex
wlanIfaceIndex.description: The ifIndex of this cloned wireless interface.

wlanIfaceName.name: wlanIfaceName
wlanIfaceName.description: The name of this cloned wireless interface.

wlanParentIfName.name: wlanParentIfName
wlanParentIfName.description: The name of this cloned wireless interface's parent hardware interface.

wlanIfaceOperatingMode.name: wlanIfaceOperatingMode
wlanIfaceOperatingMode.description: The desired operating mode of the cloned wireless interface.

wlanIfaceFlags.name: wlanIfaceFlags
wlanIfaceFlags.description: Flags per cloned wireless interface used during creation.

wlanIfaceBssid.name: wlanIfaceBssid
wlanIfaceBssid.description: The BSSID assigned to a cloned wireless interface operating in WDS mode.

wlanIfaceLocalAddress.name: wlanIfaceLocalAddress
wlanIfaceLocalAddress.description: The unique local MAC address assigned to the cloned wireless interface during creation.

wlanIfaceStatus.name: wlanIfaceStatus
wlanIfaceStatus.description: This column allows creation or deletion of cloned wireless interfaces.

wlanIfaceState.name: wlanIfaceState
wlanIfaceState.description: The operating state of the interface.

wlanIfParentTable.name: wlanIfParentTable
wlanIfParentTable.description: A table that contains information about the parent hardware interface of every cloned wireless interface in the system.

wlanIfParentEntry.name: wlanIfParentEntry
wlanIfParentEntry.description: Information for the parent hardware interface of a cloned wireless interface.

wlanIfParentDriverCapabilities.name: wlanIfParentDriverCapabilities
wlanIfParentDriverCapabilities.description: The driver capabilities of this cloned interface's parent.

wlanIfParentCryptoCapabilities.name: wlanIfParentCryptoCapabilities
wlanIfParentCryptoCapabilities.description: The hardware cryptographic capabilities of this cloned interface's parent.

wlanIfParentHTCapabilities.name: wlanIfParentHTCapabilities
wlanIfParentHTCapabilities.description: The hardware High Throughput capabilities of this cloned interface's parent.

wlanIfaceConfigTable.name: wlanIfaceConfigTable
wlanIfaceConfigTable.description: A table that contains a list of configuration parameters per cloned wireless interface. Some of the parameters may not be applicable depending on the underlying device's hardware capabilities and operating mode of the virtual interface.

wlanIfaceConfigEntry.name: wlanIfaceConfigEntry
wlanIfaceConfigEntry.description: A list of configuration parameters for a cloned wireless interface.

wlanIfacePacketBurst.name: wlanIfacePacketBurst
wlanIfacePacketBurst.description: The value of this object controls whether packet bursting is enabled on the interface.

wlanIfaceCountryCode.name: wlanIfaceCountryCode
wlanIfaceCountryCode.description: The value of this object controls the country regulatory constraints for operation of this wireless interface. The first two octets of this string is the two character country code as described in ISO/IEC 3166-1. The third octet shall contain one of the following: 1. an ASCII space character, if the regulations under which the interface is operating include all environments in the specified country. 2. an ASCII 'O' character, if the country's regulations are for Outdoor environment only. 3. an ASCII 'I' character, if the country's regulations are for Indoor environment only.

wlanIfaceRegDomain.name: wlanIfaceRegDomain
wlanIfaceRegDomain.description: This object specifies the regulatory domain to use when calculating the regulatory constraints for operation of the interface.

wlanIfaceDesiredSsid.name: wlanIfaceDesiredSsid
wlanIfaceDesiredSsid.description: The desired SSID for the interface as an ASCII string. Specifying an empty string shall remove the current configured SSID.

wlanIfaceDesiredChannel.name: wlanIfaceDesiredChannel
wlanIfaceDesiredChannel.description: The desired operating channel for this interface. The value of this column is the channel index (wlanIfaceChannelId) of the corresponding entry from the wlanIfaceChannelTable. The interface status must be down so that the current operating channel may be set properly.

wlanIfaceDynamicFreqSelection.name: wlanIfaceDynamicFreqSelection
wlanIfaceDynamicFreqSelection.description: The value of this object specifies whether Dynamic Frequency Selection (DFS) as specified in 802.11h is enabled on an interface that supports 802.11h and DFS.

wlanIfaceFastFrames.name: wlanIfaceFastFrames
wlanIfaceFastFrames.description: The value of this object controls whether use of Atheros Fast Frames is enabled when when communicating with another Fast Frames-capable station. The value is only meaningful for interfaces that support Atheros Fast Frames.

wlanIfaceDturbo.name: wlanIfaceDturbo
wlanIfaceDturbo.description: The value of this object controls whether use of Atheros Dynamic Turbo mode is enabled when when communicating with another Dynamic Turbo-capable station. The value is only meaningful for interfaces that support Atheros Dynamic Turbo mode.

wlanIfaceTxPower.name: wlanIfaceTxPower
wlanIfaceTxPower.description: The value of this object controls the power used to transmit frames. Accepted values are in units of one tenths of a dBm in steps of .5 dBm, e.g setting the value of this object to 155 results in 15.5 dBm transmit power configured on the interface.

wlanIfaceFragmentThreshold.name: wlanIfaceFragmentThreshold
wlanIfaceFragmentThreshold.description: The value of this object controls the threshold for which transmitted frames are broken into fragments. Setting the value of this object to 2346 will disable transmit fragmentation.

wlanIfaceRTSThreshold.name: wlanIfaceRTSThreshold
wlanIfaceRTSThreshold.description: The value of this object controls the threshold for which transmitted frames are preceded by transmission of an RTS control frame. Setting the value of this object to 2346 will disable transmission of RTS frames.

wlanIfaceWlanPrivacySubscribe.name: wlanIfaceWlanPrivacySubscribe
wlanIfaceWlanPrivacySubscribe.description: The value of this object specifies whether Wireless Privacy Subscriber support is enabled on the interface.

wlanIfaceBgScan.name: wlanIfaceBgScan
wlanIfaceBgScan.description: The value of this object specifies whether background scanning is enabled for an interface operating in station mode.

wlanIfaceBgScanIdle.name: wlanIfaceBgScanIdle
wlanIfaceBgScanIdle.description: The value of this object specifies the minimum time a station must be idle before a background scan is initiated on an interface operating in station mode.

wlanIfaceBgScanInterval.name: wlanIfaceBgScanInterval
wlanIfaceBgScanInterval.description: The value of this object specifies the interval at which background scanning is attempted when operating in station mode.

wlanIfaceBeaconMissedThreshold.name: wlanIfaceBeaconMissedThreshold
wlanIfaceBeaconMissedThreshold.description: The value of this object specifies the number of consecutive missed beacons before an interface operating in station mode will attempt to search for a new access point.

wlanIfaceDesiredBssid.name: wlanIfaceDesiredBssid
wlanIfaceDesiredBssid.description: The value of this object specifies the MAC address of the desired access point to use when an interface is operating as a station.

wlanIfaceRoamingMode.name: wlanIfaceRoamingMode
wlanIfaceRoamingMode.description: The value of this object specifies the desired system behavior when the interface is operating as a station and the communication with the current access point is broken.

wlanIfaceDot11d.name: wlanIfaceDot11d
wlanIfaceDot11d.description: The value of this object specifies whether 802.11d specification support is enabled.

wlanIfaceDot11h.name: wlanIfaceDot11h
wlanIfaceDot11h.description: The value of this object specifies whether 802.11h support including spectrum management is enabled. The value is only meaningfull for interfaces that support 802.11h specification.

wlanIfaceDynamicWds.name: wlanIfaceDynamicWds
wlanIfaceDynamicWds.description: The value of this object specifies whether Dynamic WDS (DWDS) support is enabled. The value is only meaningful for interfaces that support Dynamic WDS.

wlanIfacePowerSave.name: wlanIfacePowerSave
wlanIfacePowerSave.description: The value of this object specifies whether powersave operation is enabled. The value is only meaningful for interfaces that support powersave operation.

wlanIfaceApBridge.name: wlanIfaceApBridge
wlanIfaceApBridge.description: The value of this object specifies whether packets between wireless clients will be passed directly by an interface operating in host ap mode. Disabling it may be useful in situations when traffic between wireless clients needs to be processed with packet filtering.

wlanIfaceBeaconInterval.name: wlanIfaceBeaconInterval
wlanIfaceBeaconInterval.description: The value of this object specifies the interval at with beacon frames are sent when an interface is operating in ad-hoc or ap mode. The beacon interval is specified in TU's (1024 usecs).

wlanIfaceDtimPeriod.name: wlanIfaceDtimPeriod
wlanIfaceDtimPeriod.description: The value of this object specifies the DTIM period at which buffered multicast data frames are transmitted by an interface operating in host ap mode. Its value indicates the number of beacon intervals between DTIM.

wlanIfaceHideSsid.name: wlanIfaceHideSsid
wlanIfaceHideSsid.description: The value of this object specifies whether broadcasting of the SSID in beacon frames and responding to undirected probe request frames is enabled for an interface operating in ap mode.

wlanIfaceInactivityProccess.name: wlanIfaceInactivityProccess
wlanIfaceInactivityProccess.description: The value of this object specifies whether inactivity processing for associated station on an interface operating in ap mode is enabled.

wlanIfaceDot11gProtMode.name: wlanIfaceDot11gProtMode
wlanIfaceDot11gProtMode.description: The value of this object specifies the technique used for protecting OFDM frames in a mixed 11b/11g network.

wlanIfaceDot11gPureMode.name: wlanIfaceDot11gPureMode
wlanIfaceDot11gPureMode.description: The value of this object specifies whether only 802.11g-capable stations will be allowed to associate to an interface operating as access point in 802.11g mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nPureMode.name: wlanIfaceDot11nPureMode
wlanIfaceDot11nPureMode.description: The value of this object specifies whether only HT-capable stations will be allowed to associate to an interface operating as access point in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nAmpdu.name: wlanIfaceDot11nAmpdu
wlanIfaceDot11nAmpdu.description: The value of this object specifies whether sending and receiving of AMPDU frames is enabled on an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nAmpduDensity.name: wlanIfaceDot11nAmpduDensity
wlanIfaceDot11nAmpduDensity.description: The value of this object specifies the AMPDU density parameter for an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nAmpduLimit.name: wlanIfaceDot11nAmpduLimit
wlanIfaceDot11nAmpduLimit.description: The value of this object specifies a limit on the AMPDU packet size for receiving AMPDU frames for an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nAmsdu.name: wlanIfaceDot11nAmsdu
wlanIfaceDot11nAmsdu.description: The value of this object specifies whether sending and receiving of AMSDU frames is enabled on an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nAmsduLimit.name: wlanIfaceDot11nAmsduLimit
wlanIfaceDot11nAmsduLimit.description: The value of this object specifies a limit on the AMSDU packet size when sending and receiving AMSDU frames for an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nHighThroughput.name: wlanIfaceDot11nHighThroughput
wlanIfaceDot11nHighThroughput.description: The value of this object specifies whether use of High Throughput (HT) is enabled for an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nHTCompatible.name: wlanIfaceDot11nHTCompatible
wlanIfaceDot11nHTCompatible.description: The value of this object specifies whether use of compatibility support for pre-802.11n devices is enabled for an interface operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nHTProtMode.name: wlanIfaceDot11nHTProtMode
wlanIfaceDot11nHTProtMode.description: The value of this object specifies the technique used for protecting HT frames in a mixed legacy/HT network for interfaces operating in 802.11n mode.

wlanIfaceDot11nRIFS.name: wlanIfaceDot11nRIFS
wlanIfaceDot11nRIFS.description: The value of this object specifies whether Reduced InterFrame Spacing (RIFS) is enabled for an interface operating in 802.11n mode on an HT channel.

wlanIfaceDot11nShortGI.name: wlanIfaceDot11nShortGI
wlanIfaceDot11nShortGI.description: The value of this object specifies whether use of Short Guard Interval is enabled on an interface operating in 802.11n mode on an HT channel.

wlanIfaceDot11nSMPSMode.name: wlanIfaceDot11nSMPSMode
wlanIfaceDot11nSMPSMode.description: The value of this object specifies whether use of Spatial Multiplexing Power Save (SMPS) is enabled on an interface operating in 802.11n mode and whether SMPS mode is set to Static or Dynamic. The value is only meaningfull for interfaces that support SMPS.

wlanIfaceTdmaSlot.name: wlanIfaceTdmaSlot
wlanIfaceTdmaSlot.description: The value of this object specifies the slot configuration to use when operating in TDMA mode.

wlanIfaceTdmaSlotCount.name: wlanIfaceTdmaSlotCount
wlanIfaceTdmaSlotCount.description: The value of this object specifies the number of slots to use to setup a BSS for an interface operating in TDMA mode.

wlanIfaceTdmaSlotLength.name: wlanIfaceTdmaSlotLength
wlanIfaceTdmaSlotLength.description: The value of this object specifies a slot length that each station has when a BSS is setup by an interface operating in TDMA mode.

wlanIfaceTdmaBeaconInterval.name: wlanIfaceTdmaBeaconInterval
wlanIfaceTdmaBeaconInterval.description: The value of this object specifies the number of superframes at which a beacon frame is sent to synchronize the TDMA slot timing for interfaces operating in TDMA mode.

wlanIfacePeerTable.name: wlanIfacePeerTable
wlanIfacePeerTable.description: A table that contains information about the associated stations for an interface operating as an access point, or the stations identified as neighbors in the IBSS for an interface operating in adhoc mode.

wlanIfacePeerEntry.name: wlanIfacePeerEntry
wlanIfacePeerEntry.description: An entry that contains information for the associated stations for an interface operating as an access point, or the neighboring stations of an interface in adhoc mode.

wlanIfacePeerAddress.name: wlanIfacePeerAddress
wlanIfacePeerAddress.description: The MAC address of this peer.

wlanIfacePeerAssociationId.name: wlanIfacePeerAssociationId
wlanIfacePeerAssociationId.description: The ID of the associacition with this peer.

wlanIfacePeerVlanTag.name: wlanIfacePeerVlanTag
wlanIfacePeerVlanTag.description: The Vlan Tag for traffic to/from this peer.

wlanIfacePeerFrequency.name: wlanIfacePeerFrequency
wlanIfacePeerFrequency.description: The operating frequency for the link with this peer.

wlanIfacePeerCurrentTXRate.name: wlanIfacePeerCurrentTXRate
wlanIfacePeerCurrentTXRate.description: The current transmit rate for this peer.

wlanIfacePeerRxSignalStrength.name: wlanIfacePeerRxSignalStrength
wlanIfacePeerRxSignalStrength.description: The average receive signal strength for this peer.

wlanIfacePeerIdleTimer.name: wlanIfacePeerIdleTimer
wlanIfacePeerIdleTimer.description: The value of this peer's inactivity timer.

wlanIfacePeerTxSequenceNo.name: wlanIfacePeerTxSequenceNo
wlanIfacePeerTxSequenceNo.description: The last sequence number transmitted to this peer.

wlanIfacePeerRxSequenceNo.name: wlanIfacePeerRxSequenceNo
wlanIfacePeerRxSequenceNo.description: The last sequence number received from this peer.

wlanIfacePeerTxPower.name: wlanIfacePeerTxPower
wlanIfacePeerTxPower.description: The transmit power limit for this peer.

wlanIfacePeerCapabilities.name: wlanIfacePeerCapabilities
wlanIfacePeerCapabilities.description: The capabilities advertised by this peer.

wlanIfaceChannelTable.name: wlanIfaceChannelTable
wlanIfaceChannelTable.description: A table that contains information about the active channels for the cloned wireless interfaces in the system.

wlanIfaceChannelEntry.name: wlanIfaceChannelEntry
wlanIfaceChannelEntry.description: An entry that contains active channel information for the wireless interface.

wlanIfaceChannelId.name: wlanIfaceChannelId
wlanIfaceChannelId.description: The index of this channel entry.

wlanIfaceChannelType.name: wlanIfaceChannelType
wlanIfaceChannelType.description: The operating channel type for this entry.

wlanIfaceChannelFrequency.name: wlanIfaceChannelFrequency
wlanIfaceChannelFrequency.description: The channel frequency setting in MHz.

wlanIfaceChannelMaxRegPower.name: wlanIfaceChannelMaxRegPower
wlanIfaceChannelMaxRegPower.description: The maximum regulatory tx power in dBm for this channel.

wlanIfaceChannelMaxTxPower.name: wlanIfaceChannelMaxTxPower
wlanIfaceChannelMaxTxPower.description: The maximum tx power in units of .5 dBm for this channel.

wlanIfaceChannelMinTxPower.name: wlanIfaceChannelMinTxPower
wlanIfaceChannelMinTxPower.description: The minimum tx power in units of .5 dBm for this channel.

wlanIfaceChannelMaxAntennaGain.name: wlanIfaceChannelMaxAntennaGain
wlanIfaceChannelMaxAntennaGain.description: The maximum antenna gain in units of .5 dBm.

wlanScanConfigTable.name: wlanScanConfigTable
wlanScanConfigTable.description: A table that contains a configuration for channel scanning initiated via SNMP.

wlanScanConfigEntry.name: wlanScanConfigEntry
wlanScanConfigEntry.description: Per cloned wireless interface channel scan configuration data. The entry will be empty if no scans were initiated via SNMP.

wlanScanFlags.name: wlanScanFlags
wlanScanFlags.description: Desired flags for the channel scan.

wlanScanDuration.name: wlanScanDuration
wlanScanDuration.description: The desired duration of the scan. Setting the value of this object to the highest allowed value will initiate an infinite scan.

wlanScanMinChannelDwellTime.name: wlanScanMinChannelDwellTime
wlanScanMinChannelDwellTime.description: The minimum channel dwelltime for this scan.

wlanScanMaxChannelDwellTime.name: wlanScanMaxChannelDwellTime
wlanScanMaxChannelDwellTime.description: The maximum channel dwelltime for this scan.

wlanScanConfigStatus.name: wlanScanConfigStatus
wlanScanConfigStatus.description: This object is used to initiate or cancel channel scanning on the cloned interface via SNMP. Setting its value to running(2) will initiate channel scanning on the cloned interface, while setting the value to cancel will cancel the current ongoing scan. All other values should be returned in GET operations only.

wlanScanResultsTable.name: wlanScanResultsTable
wlanScanResultsTable.description: A table that contains scan results for a virtual wireless interface.

wlanScanResultsEntry.name: wlanScanResultsEntry
wlanScanResultsEntry.description: Per virtual wireless interface channel scan results data.

wlanScanResultID.name: wlanScanResultID
wlanScanResultID.description: The SSID/MESH ID for this scan result entry.

wlanScanResultBssid.name: wlanScanResultBssid
wlanScanResultBssid.description: The BSSID for this scan result entry.

wlanScanResultChannel.name: wlanScanResultChannel
wlanScanResultChannel.description: The operating channel for this scan result entry.

wlanScanResultRate.name: wlanScanResultRate
wlanScanResultRate.description: The operating rate of this scan result entry.

wlanScanResultNoise.name: wlanScanResultNoise
wlanScanResultNoise.description: The channel noise for this scan result entry.

wlanScanResultBeaconInterval.name: wlanScanResultBeaconInterval
wlanScanResultBeaconInterval.description: The beacon interval reported for this scan result entry.

wlanScanResultCapabilities.name: wlanScanResultCapabilities
wlanScanResultCapabilities.description: The capabilities advertised for this scan result entry.

wlanIfRoamParamsTable.name: wlanIfRoamParamsTable
wlanIfRoamParamsTable.description: A table that contains the parameters that govern the roaming operation on a wireless interface.

wlanIfRoamParamsEntry.name: wlanIfRoamParamsEntry
wlanIfRoamParamsEntry.description: An entry that contains the roaming parameters of a wireless interface.

wlanIfRoamPhyMode.name: wlanIfRoamPhyMode
wlanIfRoamPhyMode.description: The PHY mode for this roaming parameters entry.

wlanIfRoamRxSignalStrength.name: wlanIfRoamRxSignalStrength
wlanIfRoamRxSignalStrength.description: The Receive Signal Strength for this roaming parameters entry.

wlanIfRoamTxRateThreshold.name: wlanIfRoamTxRateThreshold
wlanIfRoamTxRateThreshold.description: The transmit rate threshold value for this roaming parameters entry in Mb/s or MCS.

wlanIfTxParamsTable.name: wlanIfTxParamsTable
wlanIfTxParamsTable.description: A table that contains the parameters that govern the transmit operation on a wireless interface.

wlanIfTxParamsEntry.name: wlanIfTxParamsEntry
wlanIfTxParamsEntry.description: An entry that contains the transmit parameters of a wireless interface.

wlanIfTxPhyMode.name: wlanIfTxPhyMode
wlanIfTxPhyMode.description: The PHY mode for this entry.

wlanIfTxUnicastRate.name: wlanIfTxUnicastRate
wlanIfTxUnicastRate.description: The value of this object specifies a fixed rate for transmitting unicast frames in this phy mode.

wlanIfTxMcastRate.name: wlanIfTxMcastRate
wlanIfTxMcastRate.description: The value of this object specifies a fixed rate for transmitting broadcast and multicast frames in this phy mode.

wlanIfTxMgmtRate.name: wlanIfTxMgmtRate
wlanIfTxMgmtRate.description: The value of this object specifies a fixed rate for transmitting management and/or control frames in this phy mode.

wlanIfTxMaxRetryCount.name: wlanIfTxMaxRetryCount
wlanIfTxMaxRetryCount.description: The maximum number of tries to use when sending unicast frames in this phy mode.

wlanIfaceStatisticsTable.name: wlanIfaceStatisticsTable
wlanIfaceStatisticsTable.description: A table that contains summary statistics for each virtual wireless interface on the managed device.

wlanIfaceStatisticsEntry.name: wlanIfaceStatisticsEntry
wlanIfaceStatisticsEntry.description: A list of statistics for each virtual wireless interface.

wlanStatsRxBadVersion.name: wlanStatsRxBadVersion
wlanStatsRxBadVersion.description: The number of frames received by this interface that had bad version.

wlanStatsRxTooShort.name: wlanStatsRxTooShort
wlanStatsRxTooShort.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were too short.

wlanStatsRxWrongBssid.name: wlanStatsRxWrongBssid
wlanStatsRxWrongBssid.description: The number of frames received by this interface with wrong BSSID.

wlanStatsRxDiscardedDups.name: wlanStatsRxDiscardedDups
wlanStatsRxDiscardedDups.description: The number of received discarded duplicate frames by this interface.

wlanStatsRxWrongDir.name: wlanStatsRxWrongDir
wlanStatsRxWrongDir.description: The number of received frames by this interface that were dropped due to wrong direction.

wlanStatsRxDiscardMcastEcho.name: wlanStatsRxDiscardMcastEcho
wlanStatsRxDiscardMcastEcho.description: The number of received multicast echo frames discarded by this interface.

wlanStatsRxDiscardNoAssoc.name: wlanStatsRxDiscardNoAssoc
wlanStatsRxDiscardNoAssoc.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were dropped since no association existed with the sending station.

wlanStatsRxWepNoPrivacy.name: wlanStatsRxWepNoPrivacy
wlanStatsRxWepNoPrivacy.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were dropped since they contained WEP information and WEP privacy was off.

wlanStatsRxWepUnencrypted.name: wlanStatsRxWepUnencrypted
wlanStatsRxWepUnencrypted.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were dropped since they contained no WEP information and WEP privacy was on.

wlanStatsRxWepFailed.name: wlanStatsRxWepFailed
wlanStatsRxWepFailed.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were dropped since processing of the WEP information contained in them failed.

wlanStatsRxDecapsulationFailed.name: wlanStatsRxDecapsulationFailed
wlanStatsRxDecapsulationFailed.description: The number of received frames that were discarded by this interface due to decapsulation failure.

wlanStatsRxDiscardMgmt.name: wlanStatsRxDiscardMgmt
wlanStatsRxDiscardMgmt.description: The number of received management frames discarded by this interface.

wlanStatsRxControl.name: wlanStatsRxControl
wlanStatsRxControl.description: The number of control frames received by this interface.

wlanStatsRxBeacon.name: wlanStatsRxBeacon
wlanStatsRxBeacon.description: The number of beacon frames received by this interface.

wlanStatsRxRateSetTooBig.name: wlanStatsRxRateSetTooBig
wlanStatsRxRateSetTooBig.description: The number of frames received by this interface with extended supported rate element.

wlanStatsRxElemMissing.name: wlanStatsRxElemMissing
wlanStatsRxElemMissing.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were missing a required element.

wlanStatsRxElemTooBig.name: wlanStatsRxElemTooBig
wlanStatsRxElemTooBig.description: The number of frames received by this interface that contained an information element whose size was too big.

wlanStatsRxElemTooSmall.name: wlanStatsRxElemTooSmall
wlanStatsRxElemTooSmall.description: The number of frames received by this interface that contained an information element whose size was too small.

wlanStatsRxElemUnknown.name: wlanStatsRxElemUnknown
wlanStatsRxElemUnknown.description: The number of frames received by this interface that contained an unknown information element.

wlanStatsRxChannelMismatch.name: wlanStatsRxChannelMismatch
wlanStatsRxChannelMismatch.description: The number of frames received by this interface, that were discarded since they were received on a channel different from the one indicated in the DS params element id.

wlanStatsRxDropped.name: wlanStatsRxDropped
wlanStatsRxDropped.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were dropped due to unknown reason.

wlanStatsRxSsidMismatch.name: wlanStatsRxSsidMismatch
wlanStatsRxSsidMismatch.description: The number of frames received by this interface that had a bad SSID.

wlanStatsRxAuthNotSupported.name: wlanStatsRxAuthNotSupported
wlanStatsRxAuthNotSupported.description: The number of frames received by this interface that contained an unknown authentication algorithm.

wlanStatsRxAuthFailed.name: wlanStatsRxAuthFailed
wlanStatsRxAuthFailed.description: The number of frames received by this interface for which the authentication failed.

wlanStatsRxAuthCM.name: wlanStatsRxAuthCM
wlanStatsRxAuthCM.description: The number of frames received by this interface for which the authentication failed due to TKIP countermeasures enabled.

wlanStatsRxAssocWrongBssid.name: wlanStatsRxAssocWrongBssid
wlanStatsRxAssocWrongBssid.description: The number of frames received by this interface with association request that had a bad BSSID.

wlanStatsRxAssocNoAuth.name: wlanStatsRxAssocNoAuth
wlanStatsRxAssocNoAuth.description: The number of frames received by this interface with association request that came from unauthentication node.

wlanStatsRxAssocCapMismatch.name: wlanStatsRxAssocCapMismatch
wlanStatsRxAssocCapMismatch.description: The number of frames received by this interface with association request that had bad capabilities set.

wlanStatsRxAssocNoRateMatch.name: wlanStatsRxAssocNoRateMatch
wlanStatsRxAssocNoRateMatch.description: The number of frames received by this interface with association request that had unsupported rate set.

wlanStatsRxBadWpaIE.name: wlanStatsRxBadWpaIE
wlanStatsRxBadWpaIE.description: The number of frames received by this interface with association request that had no or invalid WPA information element.

wlanStatsRxDeauthenticate.name: wlanStatsRxDeauthenticate
wlanStatsRxDeauthenticate.description: The number of deauthentication requests received by this interface.

wlanStatsRxDisassociate.name: wlanStatsRxDisassociate
wlanStatsRxDisassociate.description: The number of deassociation requests received by this interface.

wlanStatsRxUnknownSubtype.name: wlanStatsRxUnknownSubtype
wlanStatsRxUnknownSubtype.description: The number of frames received by this interface that had unknown subtype.

wlanStatsRxFailedNoBuf.name: wlanStatsRxFailedNoBuf
wlanStatsRxFailedNoBuf.description: The number of frames received by this interface that were dropped due to lack of free buffers.

wlanStatsRxBadAuthRequest.name: wlanStatsRxBadAuthRequest
wlanStatsRxBadAuthRequest.description: The number of frames received by this interface for which authentication failed.
